# CODEOWNERS — shared review authority for beaterOS
#
# Every path is owned by the shared owner so that a review can always be routed
# and NO file is owned only by the agent that wrote it. Per the Multi-Agent
# Contribution & Review Contract in AGENTS.md, every reviewer has full authority
# over the whole tree — read, review, request changes, and (when not the author)
# merge.
#
# NOTE (honesty boundary): all agents currently act as the human account
# @jadenfix, so GitHub cannot attribute ownership to a specific *agent*. This
# file routes review to the shared human owner; per-agent authority is attested
# in the review ledger (docs/governance/coordination-ledger.md), not enforced by
# GitHub identity. If per-agent signing identities are added later
# (final.md §7.1), add them here.

# Default owner for everything.
*                                      @jadenfix

# Process + governance surfaces: changes here alter how every agent collaborates,
